The Wizard of Odds is a game where a player is given the chance to guess a number between 1 and N. The player can ask K true/false questions to the Wizard, and the Wizard will answer them based on the secret number. The player needs to guess the secret number to win the game. 

The game can be solved if the player is given the value of K and N. The player needs to check if K is greater than or equal to the logarithm of N base 2. If it is, then the player can use binary search to find the secret number. If K is less than the logarithm of N base 2, then the player can use the pigeonhole principle to find the secret number.

In the solution function, we read the input from the standard input and split it into N and K. We then check if K is greater than or equal to the logarithm of N base 2. If it is, we use binary search to find the secret number. If K is less than the logarithm of N base 2, we use the pigeonhole principle to find the secret number. Finally, we return "Your wish is granted!" if the player can win the game, otherwise we return "You will become a flying monkey!".

max_speed = 0
prev_distance = 0
for i in range(n):
    t, d = map(int, input().split())
    time_diff = t - prev_t
    distance_diff = d - prev_distance
    speed = distance_diff / time_diff
    max_speed = max(max_speed, int(speed))
    prev_t, prev_distance = t, d
print(max_speed)
